nncompression.convert package¶

Submodules¶

nncompression.convert.to_onnx module¶

Module containing methods to convert neural network models to onnx models.

nncompression.convert.to_onnx.from_pytorch(model, dummy_data, file_name, device)[source]¶

A function to convert a pytorch model to an onnx model Once converted perform tests to ensure model is converted correctly

Parameters

  • model (torch.nn.Module) – A pytorch neural network model

  • dummy_data (tensor) – Some data that takes the shape of the neural network inputs. This doesnt have to be from training or test it can be random. ie a tensor(batch_size, input1, input2, inputn)

  • file_name (str) – location for file output

  • device (torch.device) – device for pytorch compute
